A board of inquiry has said that in total, 56 rhino horns went missing from the strong-room at the national parks headquarters. HARARE It's emerged that R40 million worth of rhino horn was stolen from a national parks strong-room almost two years ago.The authority is advertising for a new director-general in the wake of the theft.A board of inquiry has said that in total, 56 rhino horns went missing from the strong-room at the national parks headquarters.They appear to have been stolen in 2015 and the state-run Sunday Mail puts their value at $3 million.The paper says more than 4,000 rhino horns are kept there under tight security.Former director general of Zimbabwe's Parks and Wildlife Management Authority Edson Chidziya was suspended from duty over the matter last year.The authority is now advertising for someone to replace him.